description:
Jannik Sinner and Jack Draper are scheduled to play each other in a semifinal matchup in the US Open Men’s Singles Tournament on September 6, 2024.

This market will resolve to “Sinner” if Jannik Sinner wins his match against Jack Draper in the semifinals of the US Open Men’s Singles tournament.

This market will resolve to “Draper” if Jack Draper wins his match against Jannik Sinner in the semifinals of the US Open Men’s Singles tournament.

If the match ends in a tie, is canceled, or delayed beyond September 13, 2024, this market will resolve to 50-50.

The primary resolution source for this market will be official information from the US Open (ex: https://www.usopen.org/index.html) including live footage, however a consensus of credible reporting may also be used.
